article.description: — Darius McGhee's 32 points led Liberty over Central Arkansas 82-62 on Saturday night.
article.headline: McGhee scores 32 as Liberty downs Central Arkansas 82-62
article.linkText: McGhee scores 32 as Liberty downs Central Arkansas 82-62
article.story:
LYNCHBURG, Va. -- — Darius McGhee's 32 points led Liberty over Central Arkansas 82-62 on Saturday night.

McGhee added five assists for the Flames (14-5, 5-1 Atlantic Sun Conference). Colin Porter was 5-of-10 shooting (4 for 7 from distance) to add 16 points. Kyle Rode shot 4 for 9, including 3 for 6 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points.

The Bears (6-13, 1-5) were led by Camren Hunter and Johannes Kirispuu, who each finished with 14 points. Hunter added five assists and three steals. Vincent Reeves had 11 points.

NEXT UP

Liberty next plays Thursday against Jacksonville on the road, and Central Arkansas will host North Alabama on Wednesday.
